<TITLE> Indo-Bangladesh Bangla Game in January 2008 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 7 (bdnews24.com) - The Bangladesh Olympic Association (BOA) has decided to hold the 2nd Indo-Bangladesh Bangla Games in January next year at the Bangladesh Krira Shikkha Protisthan (BKSP). The decision was taken at the BOA meeting with its acting secretary general Kutubuddin Ahmed in chair Sunday. The meeting also decided to hold the inaugural ceremony of the games at the Bangabandhu National Stadium. The inaugural games was held in Kolkata in December 2006. The Games will comprise eight disciplines -- volleyball, swimming, football, kabaddi, athletics, shooting, basketball and kho kho. Except athletics, the BOA have already started the training camps for the athletes and it completed its first phase Sunday and will resume the camps after Eid-ul-Fitr. 
